thread.title: Pakistan’s Precarious Democracy

author: Sadanand Dhume
title: Pakistan’s Precarious Democracy
text:
When President Barack Obama greets Pakistan’s Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif at the White House Thursday, he will encounter a leader much diminished since Mr. Sharif visited two years ago.
In 2013 Mr. Sharif had recently been elected prime minister for the third time and appeared firmly in control of his country. Pakistan had completed its first successful transition from one elected government to another.
